JOHANNESBURG - The new trailer for Luc Besson s Valerian and the City of a Thousand Planets launches worldwide at 3.30pm South African time on Wednesday.The visually spectacular new adventure film from Besson, director of The Professional, Lucy and The Fifth Element, is based on a French comic book series that inspired artists, writers and filmmakers.In the 28th century, Valerian (Dane DeHaan) and Laureline (Cara Delevingne) are special operatives who help maintain order throughout the human territories.They embark on a mission to the astonishing city of Alpha, an ever-expanding metropolis where species from all over the universe have converged over centuries to share knowledge, intelligence and cultures with each other. But a dark force threatens the peaceful existence of the City of a Thousand Planets, and Valerian and Laureline must race to identify the marauding menace and safeguard not just Alpha but the future of the universe. The movie is to be released in cinemas on 21 July.To download the new trailer click here.eNCA